<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>AIR CONDITIONING - HEATER SYSTEM: 2000, 4000, AND 8000 - Before 12/06/1994 - REMOVE AND INSTALL - BLOWER
        MOTOR AND FAN
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>BLOWER MOTOR AND FAN</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Make sure the key switch and the blower motor switch are off or that the battery ground
                    cable has been disconnected.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the cover from the passenger side of the instrument panel.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the cover from the Blend-Air unit housing.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the blower motor wiring connector and ground wire.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the motor cooling air hose from the blower motor (if equipped).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the mounting screws and remove the blower motor assembly from the blower housing
                    (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601417">Figure 17</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1601417" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1601417" filename="../figg16/G1601417.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="352px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 17. Blower Motor Removal</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the fan lock nut and lift the fan and spacer from the motor shaft.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the fan on the motor shaft as follows:</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Position the metal spacer in the shaft hole in the fan (motor side).</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Position the fan on the motor shaft.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Install the fan lock nut and tighten to 1 to 1.25 ft-lbs. (1 to 1.7 Nm).</para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the blower motor assembly on the blower housing and install the mounting
                    screws.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the motor cooling air hose to the outlet on the blower housing (where
                    equipped).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect blower wiring connector to the ground wire.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Reconnect the battery, turn the key and blower switches ON and check motor operation.
                    After this operation check, turn both switches OFF.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Replace the covers on the Blend-Air unit and the instrument panel.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
